('81.6', 'Other procedures on spine', 'Note: Number of vertebrae\n\r The vertebral spine consists of 25 vertebrae in the following order and number:\n\r\rCervical: C1 (atlas), C2 (axis), C3, C4, C5, C6, C7\n\r\rThoracic or Dorsal: T1, T2, T3, T4, T5, T6, T7, T8, T9, T10, T11, T12\n\r\rLumbar and Sacral: L1, L2, L3, L4, L5, S1\n\r\r Coders should report only one code from the series 81.62 or 81.63 or 81.64 to show the total number of vertebrae fused on the patient.\n\r\rCode also the level and approach of the fusion or refusion (81.00-81.08, 81.30-81.39)\n', '14', '81'),
